LAtools¶

Python Package for the Reduction of LA-ICPMS Data¶

Getting Started¶

Project Info¶

  • Hosted on Github.
  • Registered on PyPi, which means:
    pip install latools
  • Documentation on ReadTheDocs (compiled automatically on new version)
  • Build checked by TravisCI
In [2]:
# import package...
import latools as la

Data Format Descriptions¶

  • .json file.
  • RegEx to identify metadata and column headings
  • numpy.genfromtext arguments for reading data
In [6]:
with open('/home/oscar/GitHub/latools/latools/resources/data_formats/UCD_dataformat.dict') as f:
    print(f.read())

{'genfromtext_args': {'delimiter': ',',
                      'skip_header': 4},
 'column_id': {'name_row': 3,
               'delimiter': ',',
               'timecolumn': 0,
               'pattern': '([A-z]{1,2}[0-9]{1,3})'},
 'meta_regex': {0: (['path'], '(.*)'),
                2: (['date', 'method'],
                    '([A-Z][a-z]+ [0-9]+ [0-9]{4}[ ]+[0-9:]+ [amp]+).* ([A-z0-9]+\.m)')},
 'unit': 'cps'
}

Workflow Synopsis¶

  1. 'Despiking'
  2. 'Laser On'/'Laser Off' Separation
  3. Background ('baseline') correction
  4. Internal Standardisation
  5. Calibration
  6. Data Selection
  7. Integration and Export

Building a UI¶

Constraints¶

  1. Build off existing code.
  2. Cross-Platform
  3. Open Source
  4. Manual
  5. Must be maintainable by me.

Prejudices¶

  1. GitHub is Great
  2. Python is Perfect

Examples I like¶

  • Dioptas - Qt-based UI for X-Ray Diffraction Data Processing. Built using pyqt, so native Python!
  • TensorBoard - Browser-based UI for TensorFlow machine learning framework... although more of a 'viewer' than a UI.

Questions¶
